#title Microsoft Manual of Style for Technical Publications


* Documenting the User Interface

** Screen

*** Windows Desktop
<example>
icon, desktop, taskbar, taskbar button, open window, Start menu, 
submenu, Start button, Quick launch bar, notification area.
</example>

*** Open window
<example>
title bar, menu bar, tool bar, Address bar, status bar, scroll bar
Minimize button, Maxmize button, Close button, 
window border, scroll box, scroll arrow, window corner
</example>

*** Browser
<example>
Internet Explorer logo, Web page, Media bar, Links bar, Address bar
</example>

*** Web page
<example>
link, banner,nevigation button, left nevigation bar
</example>

*** Document
<example>
program icon, document window, split box, split bar, view button.
</example>

** Dialog Boxes and Property Sheets

developer calls button, switch and so on as *control*.

*** Dialog Box Syntax

 - click. Use for commands, command buttons, option buttons, and options in a list, gallery, or palette.
 - select and clear. Use for check box.
 - type and select. 
 - Use bold type in procedures for dialog box titles, labels, and options. like:

On the *Tools* menu, click *Options*, and then click the *View* tab.
Select the *Bookmarks* check box.
</ul>


